sical%20music.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A54%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-67942757%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-67942757.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-67942757.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20Refuse%20to%20Give%20Readers%20Everything%20on%20a%20Platter%3A%20Vivek%20Shanbhag%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F12180213%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-01-12-at-6.01.38-PM.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKozhikode%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%E2%80%9CGlobalisation%20and%20an%20open%20market%20have%20had%20an%20immense%20impact%20on%20everyday%20lives%2C%E2%80%9D%20author%20Vivek%20Shanbhag%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20has%20come%20with%20a%20loss%20of%20ideology%2C%20which%20has%20not%20been%20replaced%20with%20anything%20else.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShanbhag%2C%20speaking%20at%20a%20session%20at%20the%20Kerala%20Literature%20Festival%20on%20Friday%20(January%2012)%20on%20his%20book%3Cem%3E%20Sakina%E2%80%99s%20Kiss%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20was%20explaining%20why%20his%20protagonist%20Venkat%20%E2%80%93%20like%20many%20others%20in%20society%20%E2%80%93%20is%20confused%2C%20and%20why%20this%20confusion%20has%20led%20to%20the%20growth%20of%20the%20right%20wing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESakina%E2%80%99s%20Kiss%3C%2Fem%3E%20follows%20a%20family%20%E2%80%93%20Venkat%2C%20his%20wife%20Viji%20and%20their%20daughter%20Rekha%20%E2%80%93%20through%20four%20days%20of%20their%20lives%2C%20as%20they%20navigate%20certain%20extraordinary%20circumstances%20and%20a%20chasm%20in%20their%20relationships%20(particularly%20Venkat%E2%80%99s%20relationships%20with%20Viji%20and%20Rekha).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShanbhag%20is%20the%20author%20of%20nine%20books%20and%20three%20plays%20in%20Kannada%2C%20and%20has%20co-translated%20U.R.%20Ananthamurthy%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EHindutva%20or%20Hind%20Swaraj%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20English.%20%3Cem%3ESakina%E2%80%99s%20Kiss%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20Shanbhag%E2%80%99s%20second%20novel%20to%20be%20translated%20to%20English%2C%20after%20%3Cem%3EGhachar%20Ghochar%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Both%20have%20been%20translated%20from%20Kannada%20by%20Srinath%20Perur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20festival%2C%20Shanbhag%20spoke%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20about%20his%20books%2C%20their%20context%20and%20more.%20Edited%20excerpts%20from%20the%20conversation%20follow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20spoke%20in%20the%20session%20today%20about%20the%20impact%20of%20globalisation%20and%20the%20changes%20that%20has%20brought%2C%20and%20the%20influence%20that%20has%20had%20on%20your%20work.%20But%20the%20way%20you%20look%20at%20some%20of%20those%20changes%20is%20rooted%20in%20the%20family%2C%20and%20the%20internal%20dynamics%20of%20families.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20kind%20of%20changes%20that%20we%20see%20%E2%80%93%20it%20is%20not%20possible%20to%20escape%20globalisation.%20And%20that%20has%20brought%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20changes.%20We%20are%20not%20in%20a%20position%20to%20say%20whether%20that%20is%20good%20or%20bad%2C%20because%20it%20is%20a%20mixed%20bag.%20It%20is%20difficult%20to%20take%20a%20stand%20on%20it.%20How%20do%20we%20feel%20any%20change%3F%20We%20feel%20the%20change%20when%20it%20impacts%20a%20person.%20In%20India%2C%20the%20family%20is%20the%20smallest%20unit%2C%20unlike%20the%20West%20where%20the%20individual%20is%20the%20smallest%20unit.%20So%20anything%20that%20impacts%20the%20family%20impacts%20us%20as%20individuals.%20And%20I%20see%20the%20changes%20brought%20in%20by%20globalisation%2C%20the%20conflict%20it%20has%20resulted%20in%2C%20has%20impacted%20families.%20And%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20I%20was%20talking%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20both%20the%20books%20that%20have%20been%20translated%20into%20English%2C%20there%20are%20male%20protagonists%20who%20have%20had%20their%20masculinities%20questioned%2C%20internally%20within%20the%20family%2C%20and%20then%20they%20act%20in%20reaction%20to%20that.%20Is%20that%20because%20of%20how%20much%20you%20see%20this%20happening%20around%20us%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20changes%20have%20happened%20in%20a%20system%20where%20women%20did%20not%20have%20access%20to%20knowledge%2C%20where%20they%20weren%E2%80%99t%20exposed%2C%20or%20where%20they%20were%20curtailed%20or%20controlled%20or%20oppressed%20in%20some%20way.%20With%20globalisation%2C%20the%20money%20that%20has%20flowed%20in%20has%20enabled%20awareness.%20The%20kind%20of%20exposure%20that%20women%20have%2C%20girl%20children%20have%2C%20has%20changed%20in%20our%20society.%20And%20I%20think%20that%20has%20brought%20out%20a%20big%20change.%20And%20that%20is%20being%20challenged%20%E2%80%93%20if%20you%20see%20in%20smaller%20places%2C%20in%20smaller%20families%2C%20everywhere%20it%20is%20being%20challenged.%20And%20there%20lies%20the%20big%20change%3B%20not%20just%20the%20challenge%2C%20but%20the%20moment%20you%20challenge%2C%20there%20is%20a%20conflict.%20I%20see%20that%20everywhere.%20And%20the%20rise%20of%20all%20that%20we%20see%20of%20the%20right%20wing%20%E2%80%93%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20my%20novel%20is%20trying%20to%20say%20%E2%80%93%20is%20a%20response%20to%20this%20challenge.%20Because%20people%20want%20to%20retain%20control%2C%20they%20want%20to%20control%20women%3A%20how%20they%20dress%2C%20what%20they%20say%2C%20everything.%20Which%20is%20why%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20there%20in%20these%20two%20novels.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20like%20I%20write%20only%20about%20this%2C%20but%20it%20so%20happened%20that%20these%20issues%20have%20seeped%20in%2C%20because%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20you%20see%20around%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EParticularly%20from%20%3Cem%3ESakina%E2%80%99s%20Kiss%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%20suggests%20you%20believe%20stories%2C%20like%20life%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20to%20have%20a%20conventional%20ending%2C%20where%20things%20are%20neatly%20wrapped%20up.%20Is%20that%20a%20fair%20assumption%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3ESee%2C%20it%20is%20also%20a%20literary%20tool%20where%20you%20have%20an%20open%20end.%20An%20open%20ending%20is%20not%20done%20because%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20how%20to%20end%20the%20story%2C%20there%20is%20a%20specific%20reason%20for%20it.%20And%20the%20reason%20is%20that%20when%20there%20are%20options%20opened%20up%2C%20and%20you%20have%20to%20choose%20one%20of%20the%20options%2C%20as%20a%20reader%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20responsibility%20that%20you%20take.%20That%20is%20a%20point%20I%20am%20trying%20to%20make.%20That%20any%20option%20that%20you%20choose%2C%20any%20ending%20that%20you%20pick%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20responsibility%20on%20you%2C%20not%20on%20the%20writer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20reason%20I%20have%20done%20that%20is%20also%20that%20today%20we%20are%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20%E2%80%93%20be%20it%20in%20TV%20debates%2C%20media%2C%20anywhere%20%E2%80%93%20people%20wanted%20everything%20to%20be%20discussed%20and%20for%20them%20to%20be%20given%20an%20opinion.%20Everything%20has%20to%20be%20given%20on%20a%20platter%2C%20people%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20think.%20Which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20problems%20today%2C%20and%20also%20it%20has%20brought%20this%20agitation%2C%20this%20discouragement%2C%20around%20questioning%20that%20we%20see.%20And%20this%20repression%20in%20the%20current%20regime%2C%20wherever%20you%20see.%20Thinking%20is%20not%20encouraged.%20And%20people%20want%20the%20writer%20to%20resolve%20everything%20and%20give%20it%20on%20a%20platter.%20I%20refuse%20to%20do%20it%20%E2%80%93%20though%20all%20my%20novels%20are%20not%20like%20this%20%E2%80%93%20because%20in%20certain%20cases%2C%20I%20would%20really%20like%20the%20reader%20to%20get%20involved%20and%20take%20responsibility%20for%20the%20ending.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20wanted%20to%20ask%20you%20about%20translations%2C%20since%20you%E2%80%99ve%20been%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20exercise.%20How%20do%20you%20make%20those%20choices%20%E2%80%93%20that%20these%20are%20the%20two%20books%20of%20yours%20that%20would%20be%20translated%20first%20to%20English%2C%20and%20also%20about%20which%20book%20you%20decided%20to%20translate%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20that%20I%20have%20chosen%20to%20translate%20is%20also%20a%20kind%20of%20a%20political%20statement.%20I%20felt%20that%20the%20book%20was%20really%20the%20need%20of%20the%20hour.%20The%20reason%20I%20got%20involved%20in%20it%20is%20also%20because%20of%20Ananthamurthy%2C%20this%20was%20his%20last%20book%20and%20more%20information%20was%20required%20to%20bring%20clarity%20to%20the%20text.%20And%20I%20thought%20I%20had%20that%20access%20%5BAnanthamurthy%20was%20Shanbhag%E2%80%99s%20father-in-law%5D%20and%20that%20how%20I%20got%20involved.%20It%E2%80%99s%20also%20a%20beautiful%20text%2C%20a%20very%20strong%20expression%20of%20the%20concerns%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Srinath%20%5BPerur%5D%2C%20I%20knew%20Srinath%20for%20a%20long%20time%20and%20he%E2%80%99s%20a%20creative%20writer%2C%20though%20he%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20published%20anything.%20I%20like%20his%20language%2C%20I%20liked%20his%20sensibility%2C%20I%20liked%20his%20book%20(the%20travelogue%20%3Cem%3EIf%20It%E2%80%99s%20Monday%20This%20Must%20Be%20Madurai%3C%2Fem%3E).%20So%20I%20went%20to%20him%20and%20asked%20him%20if%20he%20would%20want%20to%20do%20a%20translation.%20He%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20done%20any%20translations%20till%20then.%20This%20%5B%3Cem%3EGhachar%20Ghochar%3C%2Fem%3E%5D%20is%20his%20first%20translation%20ever.%20And%20that%20is%20how%20this%20relationship%20began.%20There%20is%20always%20a%20lot%20of%20discussion%2C%20there%20are%20many%20things%20that%20go%20into%20coming%20out%20with%20these%20translations.%20And%20I%20have%20thoroughly%20enjoyed%20working%20on%20both%20these%20translations%20with%20him.%20He%E2%80%99s%20a%20very%20insightful%20literary%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20recently%20had%20a%20short%20story%20out%20in%20%3Cem%3EMint%20Lounge%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%20which%20the%20protagonist%20is%20a%20writer.%20One%20of%20his%20beliefs%20is%20that%20this%20idea%20that%20writing%20happens%20better%20in%20solitude%20is%20not%20necessarily%20true.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%E2%80%99s%20making%20fun%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYes%2C%20exactly.%20Is%20that%20a%20reflection%20of%20your%20beliefs%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20story.%20I%20have%20written%20in%20all%20kinds%20of%20circumstances%2C%20because%20I%20was%20working.%20Many%20times%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20that%20choice.%20But%20it%20is%20important%20to%20disconnect%20your%20mind%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20at%20the%20time%20of%20writing%2C%20so%20that%20it%20is%20filled%20with%20your%20own%20story%2C%20your%20own%20characters%2C%20and%20it%20is%20not%20distracting.%20Because%20one%20needs%20a%20certain%20kind%20of%20heightened%20sensibility%2C%20heightened%20imagination%20to%20write.%20So%20to%20that%20extent%20that%20cut%20off%20is%20necessary%2C%20but%20it%20might%20not%20need%20to%20be%20a%20physical%20cut%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705113052000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F12180213%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-01-12-at-6.01.38-PM.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fi-refuse-to-give-readers-everything-on-a-platter-vivek-shanbhag%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20Kerala%20Literature%20Festival%2C%20Shanbhag%20spoke%20to%20The%20Wire%20about%20his%20books%2C%20their%20context%20and%20more.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fi-refuse-to-give-readers-everything